description:
Book: Basil Essential Oil: Benefits, Properties, Applications, Studies & Recipes
Author: Ann Sullivan
ASIN: B071HQSDWX


Basil essential oil has many therapeutic qualities. It is considered a diuretic, and is known to have antioxidant, antibacterial, and antiviral properties. It has a long history of being used as a decongestant and may have anti-inflammatory benefits as well.


Basil is most commonly used as a digestive aid, where it assists with easing the discomfort associated with nausea and vomiting. It has also been historically used to help combat the common cold and flu, where it eases coughing and provides respiratory relief. As an added bonus, Basil can also improve blood circulation.


This guide lists additional uses for Basil essential oil, as well as recipes for blends that call for Basil essential oil as an ingredient. Readers will also discover the safety measures and precautions to take when using Basil essential oil
